00:19:52,876 --> 00:19:54,843
-I guess you don't care
about her after all.

270
00:19:54,876 --> 00:19:58,843
[scream]

271
00:19:58,876 --> 00:20:00,776
-How foolish you are.

272
00:20:00,810 --> 00:20:01,976
Interesting.

273
00:20:02,010 --> 00:20:04,176
I find myself
getting excited just

274
00:20:04,210 --> 00:20:06,510
thinking about all the different
ways I might finish you off.

275
00:20:16,443 --> 00:20:17,376
-Rukia!

276
00:20:17,410 --> 00:20:21,376
-Finally, it's almost over.

277
00:20:21,410 --> 00:20:23,076
[scream]

278
00:20:23,110 --> 00:20:26,776
-I prefer the quick,
bloody finish.

279
00:20:26,810 --> 00:20:29,510
[groan]

280
00:20:29,543 --> 00:20:31,076
-Do it all at once.

281
00:20:31,110 --> 00:20:33,110
Let's slice her up until
her flesh and blood

282
00:20:33,143 --> 00:20:35,243
are indistinguishable
from each other.

283
00:20:35,276 --> 00:20:37,110
-Excellent.

284
00:20:37,143 --> 00:20:39,210
-You're killing her!

285
00:20:39,243 --> 00:20:40,410
Stop this, you murderer!

286
00:20:40,443 --> 00:20:41,910
-You sure are noisy.

287
00:20:41,943 --> 00:20:42,735
-Ah!

288
00:20:50,176 --> 00:20:51,099
Ichigo.

289
00:21:06,476 --> 00:21:08,876
-I feel so beautiful right now.

290
00:21:08,910 --> 00:21:11,143
-Witness the perfection
of this technique.

291
00:21:11,176 --> 00:21:14,110
-Scatter, Senbon Zakura.

292
00:21:14,143 --> 00:21:15,410
[groan]

293
00:21:26,110 --> 00:21:27,017
ICHIGO: Rukia!

294
00:21:29,543 --> 00:21:30,810
Byakuya.

295
00:21:30,843 --> 00:21:31,776
Orihime!

296
00:21:31,810 --> 00:21:32,910
Take care of the little girl.

297
00:21:32,943 --> 00:21:33,876
I'll get Ririn.

298
00:21:33,910 --> 00:21:37,010
-All right.

299
00:21:37,043 --> 00:21:38,243
-Rukia!

300
00:21:38,276 --> 00:21:40,876
-Is she all right?

301
00:21:40,910 --> 00:21:43,343
-Oh, it's you, Captain Kuchiki.

302
00:21:43,376 --> 00:21:45,043
-Send for the relief
team immediately.

303
00:21:45,076 --> 00:21:46,343
-Right away, sir.

304
00:21:46,376 --> 00:21:47,976
-How's she doing, Orihime?

305
00:21:48,010 --> 00:21:49,176
-She's all right.

306
00:21:49,210 --> 00:21:50,810
She's just unconscious.

307
00:21:50,843 --> 00:21:52,143
-Come look at Ririn, then.

308
00:21:52,176 --> 00:21:55,010
She seems to be pretty bad.

309
00:21:55,043 --> 00:21:56,743
-I-- I tried.

310
00:21:56,776 --> 00:21:58,243
-You did just fine.

311
00:21:58,276 --> 00:21:59,343
Orihime's going to fix you up.

312
00:22:06,410 --> 00:22:08,176
-Byakuya?

313
00:22:08,210 --> 00:22:10,110
[laughter]

314
00:22:14,176 --> 00:22:15,476
-My job here is done.

315
00:22:15,510 --> 00:22:16,943
For now.

316
00:22:16,976 --> 00:22:17,910
-Come back!

317
00:22:37,041 --> 00:22:39,441
[theme music]

318
00:24:07,374 --> 00:24:09,741
VOICEOVER: Rukia's brother sure
showed up in the nick of time.

319
00:24:09,774 --> 00:24:11,107
VOICEOVER: He was probably
just waiting around

320
00:24:11,141 --> 00:24:12,175
for the perfect moment.

321
00:24:12,208 --> 00:24:13,242
VOICEOVER: How tricky.

322
00:24:13,275 --> 00:24:15,975
Obviously he knows how
to make a grand entrance.

323
00:24:16,008 --> 00:24:18,075
VOICEOVER: Maybe he's more
than just a spoiled boy

324
00:24:18,108 --> 00:24:18,942
from a rich family.

325
00:24:18,975 --> 00:24:20,308
VOICEOVER: You'd
better hope he doesn't

326
00:24:20,342 --> 00:24:23,075
slice you both to
pieces later on.

327
00:24:23,108 --> 00:24:26,008
[theme music]

328
00:24:32,608 --> 00:24:34,442
VOICEOVER: Illustrated
Guide To Soul Reapers.

329
00:24:34,475 --> 00:24:35,208
VOICEOVER: Golden!

330
00:24:43,142 --> 00:24:44,875
-What a nice moon.

331
00:24:44,908 --> 00:24:46,942
-Sure is.

332
00:24:46,975 --> 00:24:48,308
-Have a cup of sake.

333
00:24:48,342 --> 00:24:48,798
-Oh.

334
00:24:48,831 --> 00:24:50,175
Thank you.

335
00:24:50,208 --> 00:24:53,008
-Oh, moon watching should
always be like this.

336
00:24:53,042 --> 00:24:56,108
MAN: Hey, what's going on
with the moon all of a sudden?

337
00:24:56,142 --> 00:24:58,008
-All of you, quit making
fun of my bald head!

338
00:24:58,042 --> 00:24:59,875
-The moon's smooth!

